---
title: "Easy Butter Bean Curry"
slug: "easy-butter-bean-curry"
description: "A quick, budget-friendly butter bean curry with warming spices and a bright lemon finish."
cuisine: "Indian-inspired"
prepMinutes: 5
cookMinutes: 27
servings: "4 servings"
diet: ["vegan"]
tags: ["butter bean curry", "lima bean curry", "one pot"]
publishedAt: "2026-01-29"

ingredients:
  - "2 tbsp neutral oil"
  - "1 large onion, finely chopped"
  - "3 cloves garlic, crushed"
  - "1 inch ginger, grated"
  - "2 large tomatoes, chopped"
  - "½ tsp salt (plus more to taste)"
  - "¼ tsp turmeric"
  - "¼ tsp cayenne"
  - "½ tsp garam masala"
  - "¼ tsp black pepper"
  - "½ tbsp ground cumin"
  - "½ tbsp ground coriander"
  - "¼ tsp cinnamon"
  - "Pinch ground cloves"
  - "4 cups cooked butter beans (or 2 cups dried, soaked)"
  - "2¼ cups water"
  - "1½–3 tbsp lemon juice"

instructions:
  - "Heat oil in a large pan and cook onions until soft and lightly golden."
  - "Add garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute until fragrant."
  - "Add tomatoes and salt. Cook until softened and jammy."
  - "Stir in all spices and cook for 2–3 minutes."
  - "Add cooked butter beans and water. Bring to a boil."
  - "Simmer 10–15 minutes until thickened."
  - "Finish with lemon juice and adjust salt."
  - "Serve hot with basmati rice."

---

## Easy Butter Bean Curry

A quick weeknight curry that’s comforting, tangy and very budget-friendly.

### Tips
- Add spinach at the end for extra greens.
- A spoon of coconut milk makes it creamier.